1
00:00:38,970 --> 00:00:40,570
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

2
00:00:40,570 --> 00:00:41,980
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

3
00:00:44,410 --> 00:00:45,450
Hello.

4
00:00:47,480 --> 00:00:48,480
Do you know me?

5
00:00:49,750 --> 00:00:50,980
You're CEO Mari Yoon.

6
00:00:53,390 --> 00:00:56,390
Is it true
you made a lobbyist offer to Belen?

7
00:00:58,120 --> 00:00:59,260
I'm not recording.

8
00:00:59,730 --> 00:01:01,630
Without your consent,
I won't release it either.

9
00:01:01,630 --> 00:01:02,760
How did you find out?

10
00:01:03,560 --> 00:01:04,830
Did someone at the hotel leak this?

11
00:01:04,830 --> 00:01:06,070
Absolutely not.

12
00:01:09,370 --> 00:01:11,370
The rumor that Lee Woo Seul is your son.

13
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:16,510
Have you heard it?

14
00:01:18,380 --> 00:01:19,380
That's ridiculous.

15
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:21,110
This is the first I'm hearing of it.

16
00:01:21,110 --> 00:01:22,750
That's why I'm asking.

17
00:01:23,420 --> 00:01:24,880
Someone gave me a tip.

18
00:01:24,880 --> 00:01:26,290
What are you trying to confirm?

19
00:01:26,790 --> 00:01:27,990
Belen? Lee Woo Seul?

20
00:01:28,190 --> 00:01:29,420
What publication are you from?

21
00:01:29,420 --> 00:01:30,490
Sungwoo Daily.

22
00:01:30,720 --> 00:01:32,430
I'm Geum Ba Ra from the culture desk.

23
00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:35,030
I've also covered Lee Woo Seul.

24
00:01:36,360 --> 00:01:38,330
Did you happen to see the article?

25
00:01:38,330 --> 00:01:40,230
It's not like I even live in Korea.

26
00:01:40,770 --> 00:01:43,100
How is Director Park Sang Jik doing?

27
00:01:44,370 --> 00:01:45,970
He retired last week.

28
00:01:46,570 --> 00:01:48,570
He had some health issues.

29
00:01:48,570 --> 00:01:49,680
What's wrong?

30
00:01:59,450 --> 00:02:00,550
Ms. Yoon?

31
00:02:13,530 --> 00:02:14,530
Are you all right?

32
00:02:16,570 --> 00:02:17,700
You're a reporter from where again?

33
00:02:18,470 --> 00:02:19,910
Geum Ba Ra from Sungwoo Daily.

34
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:23,240
What were we talking about?

35
00:02:26,010 --> 00:02:27,610
She's old enough to have already left
the orphanage,

36
00:02:27,610 --> 00:02:30,880
so on a hunch,
I searched all the self-reliance centers,

37
00:02:31,020 --> 00:02:33,220
and Kim Jin Ju was the only person
who matched.

38
00:02:33,220 --> 00:02:34,290
A woman?

39
00:02:34,350 --> 00:02:36,120
Yes, and she's exactly 27.

40
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:39,590
Thank you.

41
00:02:40,290 --> 00:02:41,290
Good work.

42
00:02:45,130 --> 00:02:47,130
Was it because I was thinking
about Momo too much?

43
00:02:48,370 --> 00:02:50,670
But why did CEO Yoon all of a sudden...

44
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:52,810
How did you score the Mari Yoon interview?

45
00:02:54,410 --> 00:02:55,540
I just got lucky.

46
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:02,150
(Manager, Self-Reliance Program)

47
00:03:03,580 --> 00:03:05,180
Hello, sir.

48
00:03:05,180 --> 00:03:07,450
- Hey, it's been a while.
- Yes.

49
00:03:07,820 --> 00:03:09,490
You might want to brace yourself for this.

50
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:12,990
Someone came by asking
for your contact information.

51
00:03:13,830 --> 00:03:16,430
He said you might be
his long-lost daughter.

52
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:18,000
Who was it?

53
00:03:18,300 --> 00:03:20,000
He said he's lived abroad for a long time,

54
00:03:20,630 --> 00:03:23,100
so you'll have to meet him
to hear the details for yourself.

55
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:26,270
Should I text you the number?

56
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,240
Yes, please.

57
00:03:28,510 --> 00:03:29,680
He seemed like a nice person.

58
00:03:30,580 --> 00:03:32,510
You can arrange to meet him here
at our office if you want.

59
00:03:33,550 --> 00:03:34,980
Thank you.

60
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:45,090
- Hi.
- Hi.

61
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:46,190
Kim Jin Ju!

62
00:03:46,260 --> 00:03:48,830
A student with pierced ears?
What's this?

63
00:03:54,130 --> 00:03:55,130
Sir.

64
00:03:58,270 --> 00:03:59,970
Please give me back my earrings.

65
00:04:00,770 --> 00:04:03,480
When I was left at the orphanage,

66
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:06,150
they said these were in the blanket
I was wrapped in.

67
00:04:07,510 --> 00:04:09,150
If I wear them around,

68
00:04:10,350 --> 00:04:13,650
I was hoping my parents might see them.

69
00:04:14,390 --> 00:04:16,560
That's quite a fantasy you've got there.

70
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:19,190
If I make an exception for you,
what about the other students?

71
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:22,930
I'll let it slide just this once.

72
00:04:25,260 --> 00:04:26,600
Even if they did see them,

73
00:04:27,230 --> 00:04:29,570
do you think they'd say
they were the ones who abandoned you,

74
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:30,700
and it was nice to see you?

75
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:33,310
And he calls himself a teacher.

76
00:04:34,710 --> 00:04:37,740
I'm jealous.
I don't have anything like that, you know.

77
00:04:39,950 --> 00:04:43,420
I feel like it'd be better
if I at least had a keepsake like that.

78
00:04:44,850 --> 00:04:46,920
I'd feel less like I was just abandoned.

79
00:04:49,020 --> 00:04:51,060
But was there any love in it?

80
00:04:52,290 --> 00:04:53,560
Spicy rice cakes,
blood sausage, fried food...

81
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:56,500
And add an egg.

82
00:05:06,110 --> 00:05:07,870
This is Kim Jin Ju.

83
00:05:08,510 --> 00:05:09,840
Is now a good time to talk?

84
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:15,480
Hello?

85
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,150
Is this Kim Jin Ju?

86
00:05:18,820 --> 00:05:19,820
Yes.

87
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:22,390
Did Kim Min Hyeok, the manager
at the Self-Reliance Center, brief you?

88
00:05:22,460 --> 00:05:23,460
Yes.

89
00:05:23,460 --> 00:05:24,820
Can we meet today?

90
00:05:26,430 --> 00:05:28,460
I get off work late. Is that all right?

91
00:05:28,660 --> 00:05:30,730
That's fine. I don't mind how late.

92
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:33,370
How about around nine, then?

93
00:05:37,270 --> 00:05:38,870
Where should we meet?

94
00:05:43,310 --> 00:05:45,540
All right, quiet on set, please.
We're about to roll.

95
00:05:46,910 --> 00:05:47,910
All right, ready.

96
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:50,720
Action!

97
00:05:56,290 --> 00:05:58,360
- Cut! It's no good.
- Let's do it again.

98
00:06:01,730 --> 00:06:02,930
I need to talk to you for a sec.

99
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:08,500
Are you here for a story?

100
00:06:09,340 --> 00:06:11,640
- Yes.
- My birth father showed up.

101
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:12,940
He wants to see me.

102
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:15,610
I'm meeting him
in the Sera Hotel lounge later.

103
00:06:15,610 --> 00:06:17,810
Can you come with me?
I'm too nervous to go alone.

104
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:21,250
I have an interview
with Jin Yi Han after this.

105
00:06:25,220 --> 00:06:26,590
How did he contact you?

106
00:06:29,190 --> 00:06:30,190
I guess...

107
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:34,390
all the kids who suffered
because of Ye Jeong...

108
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:39,630
will say she got what she deserved.

109
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:43,370
As her mother, I'm to blame too.

110
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:47,040
If only I'd known
how she was behaving at school,

111
00:06:47,910 --> 00:06:51,580
I would've met with the kids she hurt,
even belatedly, and apologized.

112
00:06:52,450 --> 00:06:55,980
I should've tried to make it up to them,
but I didn't.

113
00:06:57,520 --> 00:06:59,420
But it's too late for regrets now.

114
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:02,760
I don't know what to say.

115
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:06,860
I feel terrible about it too.

116
00:07:08,630 --> 00:07:09,730
It must be karma.

117
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:13,470
They say you reap what you sow,

118
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:17,270
and it seems like
the skies are truly watching.

119
00:07:18,270 --> 00:07:21,540
The saying "spare the rod,
spoil the child" is true too.

120
00:07:23,180 --> 00:07:24,410
The reason I wanted to see you...

121
00:07:25,710 --> 00:07:27,780
My father-in-law agrees to this as well...

122
00:07:29,080 --> 00:07:33,150
How would you feel about
becoming part of our family?

123
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:36,060
We'd make it official, legally.

124
00:07:37,260 --> 00:07:40,130
To put it plainly, we want to adopt you.

125
00:07:42,130 --> 00:07:44,530
That day you came to our house...

126
00:07:44,730 --> 00:07:47,070
left such a deep impression on me.

127
00:07:48,370 --> 00:07:51,540
I just couldn't stop thinking about...

128
00:07:51,770 --> 00:07:53,470
how well you turned out,
even without parents.

129
00:07:54,070 --> 00:07:57,880
If only Ye Jeong were
half as wonderful as you...

130
00:07:58,640 --> 00:08:02,110
I know you won't see us as parents yet,
or yourself as our daughter,

131
00:08:02,250 --> 00:08:03,920
but we'd grow on each other over time.

132
00:08:05,220 --> 00:08:07,850
We'll be your safety net.

133
00:08:08,420 --> 00:08:09,490
That's what we want to do for you.

134
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:14,030
This isn't just out of a desire
to atone for Ye Jeong's awful behavior.

135
00:08:14,430 --> 00:08:16,300
We're not doing this just
to ease our own conscience.

136
00:08:17,060 --> 00:08:19,300
We've genuinely grown to care for you.

137
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,070
I'm not as good a person
as you think...

138
00:08:23,070 --> 00:08:24,670
I have many shortcomings,

139
00:08:26,370 --> 00:08:28,010
and you might be disappointed.

140
00:08:28,010 --> 00:08:31,080
Could you be worse than Ye Jeong?

141
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:36,880
I never imagined she was going around
acting like that.

142
00:08:38,750 --> 00:08:40,990
Now that she's cut us off and left,

143
00:08:42,990 --> 00:08:44,620
I'm trying my best not to think about her.

144
00:08:46,730 --> 00:08:48,890
I just hope that, wherever she is,
her spirit is repentant.

145
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:54,970
So what are you going to do?

146
00:08:56,900 --> 00:08:58,070
Should I even need to ask?

147
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:02,880
This is what we always wished for.

148
00:09:06,010 --> 00:09:07,010
Well, good for you.

149
00:09:08,050 --> 00:09:11,120
You're getting sophisticated parents
from a loaded family.

150
00:09:12,280 --> 00:09:13,590
I'll still look out for you.

151
00:09:14,820 --> 00:09:15,820
How?

152
00:09:16,790 --> 00:09:18,560
By buying me a nice meal once in a while?

153
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:25,660
They know you well, so I'm sure
they'll care about you too.

154
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:29,070
They came to volunteer last week
and acted all friendly with me.

155
00:09:29,130 --> 00:09:31,400
They're planning to keep volunteering,
you know.

156
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:33,940
And that's supposed to erase
all the pain we suffered?

157
00:09:34,710 --> 00:09:36,180
They're just doing it
to ease their own conscience.

158
00:09:36,740 --> 00:09:39,580
Either way, they're people to look up to,
aren't they?

159
00:09:39,650 --> 00:09:42,150
They should've just raised their kid right
in the first place.

160
00:09:42,410 --> 00:09:43,850
Was Tae Ye Jeong even human?

161
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:48,520
So this is how...

162
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:52,260
our friendship ends.

163
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:53,430
Why would it end?

164
00:09:53,430 --> 00:09:56,100
It won't.
We'll just be living in different places.

165
00:09:56,230 --> 00:09:58,100
But that "different place" is
a completely different...

166
00:09:59,670 --> 00:10:02,270
You're becoming the legitimate daughter
of a lawyer at a top Seoul firm.

167
00:10:02,470 --> 00:10:04,600
You'll get to enjoy everything
that Tae Ye Jeong had,

168
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:07,970
and our paths in life will diverge.

169
00:10:11,740 --> 00:10:12,780
I'm happy for you.

170
00:10:14,380 --> 00:10:15,380
Congratulations.

171
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:19,490
Congratulations.

172
00:10:20,150 --> 00:10:21,490
This is such a surprise.

173
00:10:22,520 --> 00:10:25,390
It feels like a dream.
I really hope he's my dad.

174
00:10:34,830 --> 00:10:37,200
Are you Kim Young Jun, by any chance?

175
00:10:38,370 --> 00:10:39,370
Yes.

176
00:10:45,810 --> 00:10:46,810
Have you had dinner?

177
00:10:47,310 --> 00:10:49,210
We can get a simple meal here.

178
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:50,480
Have you eaten?

179
00:10:51,050 --> 00:10:53,390
(Gimpo International Airport)

180
00:10:55,920 --> 00:10:57,290
What about the name Kim Jin Ju?

181
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:01,590
It's just what I was named,
and what I've always been called.

182
00:11:02,090 --> 00:11:03,860
Was there a necklace with the baby's name,
by any chance?

183
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:09,270
When I left her with a close friend
in Japan,

184
00:11:09,770 --> 00:11:10,770
I put it around her neck.

185
00:11:11,070 --> 00:11:14,140
I do have an earring.
A single pearl earring.

186
00:11:14,470 --> 00:11:17,280
- A pearl earring?
- They said it was in my baby blanket.

187
00:11:22,210 --> 00:11:24,080
So it's not me?

188
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:25,920
No, I don't know.

189
00:11:27,150 --> 00:11:30,690
Someone could've swapped the gold necklace
for a pearl earring.

190
00:11:31,060 --> 00:11:34,530
It's a 14-karat gold post with a pearl.
It's not expensive.

191
00:11:34,660 --> 00:11:36,760
Did you ever hear anything
about coming from Japan?

192
00:11:38,030 --> 00:11:39,030
Me?

193
00:11:40,330 --> 00:11:41,330
No.

194
00:11:42,030 --> 00:11:44,570
Anything at all, no matter how small.

195
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:51,380
There used to be a church
in Myeonghui-dong...

196
00:11:51,710 --> 00:11:55,410
affiliated with the Nua Children’s Home.
It was sold after the pastor passed away.

197
00:11:57,320 --> 00:12:00,320
I was apparently left in their baby box.

198
00:12:04,290 --> 00:12:06,930
I heard most of what I know
from that church.

199
00:12:07,860 --> 00:12:10,560
Some kids were left by parents
who couldn't afford to keep them,

200
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:13,970
and others were there to escape
abuse from their parents.

201
00:12:15,100 --> 00:12:17,200
Was there anything else in your blanket,
like a note?

202
00:12:18,170 --> 00:12:19,540
Nothing besides the earring...

203
00:12:21,140 --> 00:12:22,140
Blood type?

204
00:12:23,180 --> 00:12:24,180
Type A.

205
00:12:24,680 --> 00:12:25,680
I'm Type A too.

206
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:30,180
If I were the one left in Japan,

207
00:12:30,950 --> 00:12:33,590
wouldn't I be in an institution
somewhere in Japan?

208
00:12:34,620 --> 00:12:36,720
After looking into it,
someone brought her...

209
00:12:37,060 --> 00:12:38,160
to Korea right away.

210
00:12:39,890 --> 00:12:42,390
We should get tested to be sure.

211
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:45,560
Okay.

212
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:55,910
Didn't you check my texts?

213
00:12:59,580 --> 00:13:01,450
The ceiling is leaking.

214
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:04,620
I called management,
but they said the owner was abroad.

215
00:13:06,150 --> 00:13:07,990
If this is uncomfortable for you,
I'll go to a hotel.

216
00:13:11,660 --> 00:13:15,390
When you decided to become an actor,
how did your parents react?

217
00:13:15,530 --> 00:13:18,030
My father didn't speak to me for a month.

218
00:13:19,100 --> 00:13:20,370
We'll just have to wait and see.

219
00:13:35,510 --> 00:13:37,450
My car isn't being delivered
until next month.

220
00:13:37,980 --> 00:13:39,720
I can take the subway.

221
00:13:44,660 --> 00:13:46,630
See you Monday at ten, then.

222
00:13:47,460 --> 00:13:48,460
Okay.

223
00:13:54,470 --> 00:13:55,670
Drive safely, please.

224
00:13:55,970 --> 00:13:56,970
Will do.

225
00:14:15,220 --> 00:14:16,860
I'll be pretty busy through next week,

226
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:19,590
so let's aim for the week after next.

227
00:14:19,830 --> 00:14:21,360
But if you'd just reconsider...

228
00:14:24,900 --> 00:14:25,930
Mind if I sit here?

229
00:14:30,740 --> 00:14:31,870
I was with a client too.

230
00:14:33,170 --> 00:14:34,210
I just saw them off.

231
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:35,940
Was that an interview with Jin Yi Han?

232
00:14:36,240 --> 00:14:38,810
- Yes.
- Why were you so chummy in the interview?

233
00:14:40,210 --> 00:14:42,280
You barely made eye contact with me
during my interview.

234
00:14:42,850 --> 00:14:44,650
But you couldn't take your eyes off
Jin Yi Han.

235
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:46,950
Am I supposed to look away
while he's answering my questions?

236
00:14:47,820 --> 00:14:49,090
Why the sudden formality?

237
00:14:49,490 --> 00:14:51,120
I suppose I'm just on edge.

238
00:14:51,660 --> 00:14:53,830
Are you on edge, or are you embarrassed?

239
00:14:55,560 --> 00:14:56,700
Because I saw right through you?

240
00:14:58,100 --> 00:14:59,770
This is just like the old you.

241
00:15:00,030 --> 00:15:02,470
- You're joking around again.
- I'm not joking.

242
00:15:02,940 --> 00:15:04,770
If I didn't know better,
I'd have thought he was your boyfriend.

243
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:10,110
Let's do some serious drinking.
Tomorrow's the weekend.

244
00:15:13,580 --> 00:15:15,380
A bottle of 25-year Dickel, please.

245
00:15:15,680 --> 00:15:16,680
Right away, sir.

246
00:15:17,150 --> 00:15:18,850
Isn't that crazy expensive?

247
00:15:21,450 --> 00:15:22,450
Isn't that heavy?

248
00:15:22,820 --> 00:15:23,890
What if it is?

249
00:15:26,790 --> 00:15:27,830
You have a driver's license, right?

250
00:15:29,060 --> 00:15:31,200
I've decided on your birthday gift.
When's your birthday?

251
00:15:36,470 --> 00:15:38,800
You'll celebrate it at some point,
won't you?

252
00:15:39,910 --> 00:15:42,670
Since when are we close enough
for you to buy me a car?

253
00:15:43,540 --> 00:15:44,580
How could you say that?

254
00:15:45,380 --> 00:15:46,850
You're disappointing me
on so many levels today.

255
00:15:51,650 --> 00:15:53,050
Did you pick this place?

256
00:15:53,950 --> 00:15:56,220
- No.
- Don't you think he has a thing for you?

257
00:15:56,560 --> 00:15:58,390
Of course not. I'm just a reporter.

258
00:15:58,390 --> 00:16:00,160
You're a reporter, but also a woman.

259
00:16:01,230 --> 00:16:03,660
You really run hot and cold sometimes.

260
00:16:05,030 --> 00:16:06,800
That's a hurtful thing to say.

261
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:08,730
I'm not just talking about right now.

262
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:12,100
Last time we were here,
you just ditched me and left.

263
00:16:12,940 --> 00:16:15,370
- I had an urgent assignment.
- Don't make excuses.

264
00:16:15,810 --> 00:16:17,080
I'm not that clueless.

265
00:16:17,410 --> 00:16:19,410
Back then...

266
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:23,580
Put yourself in my shoes.

267
00:16:23,780 --> 00:16:24,850
Let's say I...

268
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:30,290
(Ba Ra)

269
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:42,670
The person you are calling is unavailable.

270
00:16:42,670 --> 00:16:45,670
Please leave a message after the tone.

271
00:16:53,610 --> 00:16:57,320
What if I only had eyes
for Director Shin Ju Shin?

272
00:16:57,820 --> 00:16:59,790
Since he's with Momo,

273
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:02,090
wouldn't I seem pathetic to you?

274
00:17:03,690 --> 00:17:04,760
Pathetic?

275
00:17:06,090 --> 00:17:07,260
Now you get it.

276
00:17:07,330 --> 00:17:09,360
You're saying you thought
I was pathetic back then.

277
00:17:11,330 --> 00:17:12,360
It's different.

278
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:15,970
I'll drink it straight.

279
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:31,020
It is completely different.

280
00:17:31,020 --> 00:17:32,420
How much does it take you to get drunk?

281
00:17:32,750 --> 00:17:34,920
- I don't know.
- Meaning you can hold your liquor?

282
00:17:35,490 --> 00:17:36,920
Or you've just never drunk enough
to find out?

283
00:17:37,020 --> 00:17:39,220
You have to let your guard down
to get drunk,

284
00:17:39,590 --> 00:17:41,190
and I've pretty much never done that.

285
00:17:42,030 --> 00:17:43,900
I've even faked being drunk when I had to.

286
00:17:44,300 --> 00:17:45,930
I'm an expert at
secretly dumping my drinks.

287
00:17:46,330 --> 00:17:47,500
Don't do that tonight.

288
00:17:48,170 --> 00:17:49,270
This is too good to waste.

289
00:17:51,740 --> 00:17:52,740
Hey.

290
00:17:53,340 --> 00:17:54,340
Yes?

291
00:17:55,040 --> 00:17:56,240
I just felt like calling you.

292
00:18:03,950 --> 00:18:05,250
You won't let your guard down,
even with me?

293
00:18:08,450 --> 00:18:09,890
It's not like you're a stranger to me,

294
00:18:10,020 --> 00:18:11,790
and I'm not drinking because it's work.

295
00:18:15,330 --> 00:18:16,400
When...

296
00:18:17,230 --> 00:18:18,630
are you the happiest?

297
00:18:21,070 --> 00:18:22,100
I'm happy...

298
00:18:23,140 --> 00:18:25,570
- right now.
- Besides right now?

299
00:18:25,840 --> 00:18:28,070
- What about you?
- Me too. Right now.

300
00:18:28,510 --> 00:18:30,810
- It's nice.
- But I'm happy.

301
00:18:31,480 --> 00:18:32,880
It's just "nice" for you?

302
00:18:33,210 --> 00:18:35,850
Coming from me,
"nice" is the highest praise.

303
00:18:43,290 --> 00:18:44,360
Shin Ju Shin...

304
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:47,390
is someone women would fall for.

305
00:18:48,630 --> 00:18:49,830
Do you like Director Shin too?

306
00:18:51,360 --> 00:18:52,360
Yes.

307
00:18:53,430 --> 00:18:55,100
He's got it all.

308
00:18:58,570 --> 00:19:02,170
His father passed away,
but he's the son of the esteemed Chairman.

309
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:04,510
As the Chairman's son?

310
00:19:11,480 --> 00:19:12,480
How about...

311
00:19:13,450 --> 00:19:14,820
we trade houses?

312
00:19:15,790 --> 00:19:17,090
When I was at your place,

313
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:19,520
it felt so comfortable and cozy.

314
00:19:20,590 --> 00:19:21,960
I feel like I'd sleep well there.

315
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:26,300
It's not really my place.
Technically, it's An Hee's.

316
00:19:27,870 --> 00:19:28,870
Having trouble sleeping?

317
00:19:29,430 --> 00:19:30,700
I wouldn't call it insomnia.

318
00:19:31,440 --> 00:19:34,510
After living in such a big villa,
you'd feel cooped up.

319
00:19:35,870 --> 00:19:38,510
Besides, if you're alone,
it'll probably be the same everywhere.

320
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:50,860
Slow down.

321
00:19:53,730 --> 00:19:55,260
Worried I'll get drunk and come on to you?

322
00:19:56,030 --> 00:19:57,160
I'm worried it'll be hard on you.

323
00:19:59,660 --> 00:20:02,730
A hangover is the least of my worries.

324
00:20:04,540 --> 00:20:08,170
Don't worry. I don't act out when drunk.
I've seen enough of it to be sick of it.

325
00:20:08,310 --> 00:20:10,910
I bet you making a scene
would be something to see.

326
00:20:11,340 --> 00:20:13,210
- To me, no matter what you do...
- Don't make me cuss at you.

327
00:20:13,280 --> 00:20:14,280
Go ahead.

328
00:20:14,850 --> 00:20:16,750
I'll even let you hit me today.

329
00:20:20,120 --> 00:20:22,520
- There's nothing I like here.
- What?

330
00:20:23,320 --> 00:20:24,420
Want me to order you spicy rice cakes?

331
00:20:25,220 --> 00:20:27,930
A long time ago,
I was standing outside a supermarket...

332
00:20:28,730 --> 00:20:29,760
Go on.

333
00:20:31,130 --> 00:20:33,060
I went there to eat snacks
to make myself feel better...

334
00:20:33,060 --> 00:20:34,930
after my teacher hurt me,

335
00:20:36,130 --> 00:20:37,400
but I couldn't buy anything.

336
00:20:42,310 --> 00:20:44,310
I saw all the other kids there
with their moms.

337
00:20:45,540 --> 00:20:47,310
And another was holding
their grandma's hand.

338
00:20:49,950 --> 00:20:54,090
In front of all those happy kids,
I felt so pathetic and small.

339
00:20:59,820 --> 00:21:01,060
We'll stop by a convenience store
on the way.

340
00:21:02,590 --> 00:21:06,200
You should either get a puppy
or find someone.

341
00:21:06,260 --> 00:21:07,800
There is no need to force
myself into a relationship.

342
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:09,770
It'd help you relax and sleep better.

343
00:21:10,440 --> 00:21:13,040
If I can't sleep, I read or play games.

344
00:21:13,370 --> 00:21:16,010
- There's plenty to do.
- I'd love to get a puppy.

345
00:21:17,510 --> 00:21:18,580
You must be lonely.

346
00:21:19,280 --> 00:21:20,350
Want me to get you one?

347
00:21:20,580 --> 00:21:22,950
I can't just leave it alone all day.
That would be cruel.

348
00:21:25,280 --> 00:21:26,520
Why don't you move in with me?

349
00:21:28,290 --> 00:21:30,090
I'm not kidding. I've got spare rooms.

350
00:21:33,490 --> 00:21:34,530
Aren't you going to get married?

351
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:37,030
You want people to think
we're living together?

352
00:21:37,260 --> 00:21:39,900
We would be.
We decided we'd live like family.

353
00:21:41,270 --> 00:21:42,270
So let's do it.

354
00:21:45,670 --> 00:21:46,940
Are you worried it'd ruin
my marriage chances?

355
00:21:47,210 --> 00:21:49,270
I'll just have to move out
again eventually.

356
00:21:49,940 --> 00:21:51,580
What woman would be okay with that?

357
00:21:51,980 --> 00:21:53,480
I'd basically be getting kicked out then.

358
00:21:55,010 --> 00:21:56,980
I don't want things to end
like that between us.

359
00:21:57,950 --> 00:22:01,350
Having a puppy is nice
for the companionship,

360
00:22:03,120 --> 00:22:06,090
but I want to be able to say "I love you."

361
00:22:08,560 --> 00:22:09,660
I've never been able to.

362
00:22:12,330 --> 00:22:13,370
Come to think of it, me neither.

363
00:22:15,900 --> 00:22:19,070
Not even to your parents?
Or to James?

364
00:22:19,370 --> 00:22:20,870
You really don't get guys, do you?

365
00:22:21,510 --> 00:22:22,570
To my own brother?

366
00:22:23,780 --> 00:22:25,510
There's so much I don't know.

367
00:22:25,840 --> 00:22:27,850
The hardest part for me
after my mom passed away...

368
00:22:30,650 --> 00:22:32,380
was never telling her I loved her.

369
00:22:33,990 --> 00:22:35,150
Not even once.

370
00:22:35,690 --> 00:22:36,690
Or rather, I didn't.

371
00:22:37,360 --> 00:22:39,360
I never thought she'd
pass away so suddenly.

372
00:22:40,630 --> 00:22:42,890
Then tell her now, in your heart.

373
00:22:43,430 --> 00:22:45,630
Like a prayer, every night
before you go to sleep.

374
00:22:46,230 --> 00:22:49,030
I'm sure she'll feel it.
The prayer from her loving son.

375
00:22:51,100 --> 00:22:52,140
You think she'll feel it?

376
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:53,810
Yes.

377
00:22:54,510 --> 00:22:59,210
If it were me, I'd stay by my son's side
and protect him, even as a spirit.

378
00:23:15,330 --> 00:23:17,860
Let me pour you a drink.
You're not just anybody.

379
00:23:20,370 --> 00:23:21,500
Say that again...

380
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:24,200
one more time.

381
00:23:28,870 --> 00:23:30,440
You're not just anybody.

382
00:23:31,140 --> 00:23:32,480
So we have something special, right?

383
00:23:36,150 --> 00:23:38,380
I'm definitely getting drunk tonight.

384
00:23:48,530 --> 00:23:51,100
You want to say "I love you" to a puppy?

385
00:23:51,260 --> 00:23:54,600
Yes. Someone to love and care for.

386
00:23:55,430 --> 00:23:57,240
I wish I had someone like that in my life.

387
00:23:58,400 --> 00:23:59,700
Wouldn't I be a better choice...

388
00:24:00,670 --> 00:24:02,070
than a dog?

389
00:24:08,580 --> 00:24:09,580
I love you.

390
00:24:14,220 --> 00:24:15,250
I didn't mean it.

391
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:22,530
A dog only has eyes for its owner,
and they never waver.

392
00:24:23,660 --> 00:24:25,500
They're animals that deserve to be loved.

393
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:29,730
What am I to you?

394
00:24:30,700 --> 00:24:33,300
I'm very clear on what you are to me.

395
00:24:35,940 --> 00:24:37,080
Clear in what way?

396
00:24:39,380 --> 00:24:41,710
That I'm definitely like a little sister,
six years younger?

397
00:24:42,710 --> 00:24:43,720
Something that will never change.

398
00:24:45,250 --> 00:24:46,790
So you don't want to be
a distant benefactor,

399
00:24:47,250 --> 00:24:49,250
but someone closer to me?

400
00:24:52,790 --> 00:24:53,790
That's right.

401
00:24:54,890 --> 00:24:57,860
Anyway, a true bond is
something that doesn't change.

402
00:24:58,160 --> 00:24:59,430
Just like the bond
between a parent and child.

403
00:25:01,670 --> 00:25:02,870
What, are we family now?

404
00:25:08,670 --> 00:25:11,580
In TV shows, when a mom says to her kids,

405
00:25:11,780 --> 00:25:13,040
or a daughter to her mom,

406
00:25:14,150 --> 00:25:16,050
"I love you,"

407
00:25:18,020 --> 00:25:20,590
I've always wondered what that felt like.

408
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:24,960
I love you.

409
00:25:28,590 --> 00:25:30,330
I'll always love you,

410
00:25:30,600 --> 00:25:31,600
my sweet girl.

411
00:25:36,030 --> 00:25:37,800
Today's the day we confessed
our love to each other.

412
00:25:38,770 --> 00:25:39,770
Remember this.

413
00:25:45,210 --> 00:25:46,210
Long time no see.

414
00:25:47,450 --> 00:25:48,450
My gosh.

415
00:25:50,050 --> 00:25:51,280
He's someone I'm interviewing.

416
00:25:52,220 --> 00:25:53,950
He was a senior in my college club.

417
00:25:54,790 --> 00:25:57,790
- And your name, sir?
- Ha Yong Joong.

418
00:25:57,860 --> 00:25:58,920
I'm Yoo Seon Oh.

419
00:26:00,390 --> 00:26:02,030
We just finished round one,
and this is round two for us.

420
00:26:03,160 --> 00:26:05,030
We haven't met, have we?

421
00:26:06,560 --> 00:26:08,230
Your friends are waiting for you.

422
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:09,470
Keep in touch.

423
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:12,440
We're in the same business,
but I never see you.

424
00:26:12,700 --> 00:26:13,710
Sure.

425
00:26:14,140 --> 00:26:15,140
Then.

426
00:26:17,510 --> 00:26:18,780
Wait a second.

427
00:26:18,780 --> 00:26:21,210
Are you that...

428
00:26:21,580 --> 00:26:22,610
WorldNet?

429
00:26:23,380 --> 00:26:25,280
- Yes.
- It's an honor.

430
00:26:27,620 --> 00:26:28,620
(Taewon Daily, Yoo Seon Oh)

431
00:26:28,820 --> 00:26:29,950
I don't have a business card on me...

432
00:26:30,490 --> 00:26:34,260
- How about a picture instead...
- He's being interviewed.

433
00:26:35,460 --> 00:26:39,200
I'm a huge fan of Lost Knights.
You owe me a meal.

434
00:26:39,630 --> 00:26:41,100
- Yes, anytime...
- You promise?

435
00:26:41,700 --> 00:26:43,030
- Okay.
- She's our witness.

436
00:26:45,370 --> 00:26:46,740
- Until then.
- Right.

437
00:26:55,350 --> 00:26:56,680
Let's have a proper drink next time.

438
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:03,490
- Keep the bottle for us. Check, please.
- Yes, sir.

439
00:27:04,060 --> 00:27:06,460
- Should we go see Ju Shin?
- You should go.

440
00:27:06,520 --> 00:27:08,590
- Together.
- Why would I go?

441
00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:11,760
Ju Shin needs to accept you
as my little sister now.

442
00:27:12,430 --> 00:27:14,300
Would you like that if you were him?

443
00:27:15,030 --> 00:27:16,030
Why wouldn't he?

444
00:27:16,300 --> 00:27:18,300
He said he doesn't tolerate people
crossing boundaries.

445
00:27:18,500 --> 00:27:20,740
Ju Shin said that to you?

446
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:23,640
He summoned me once.

447
00:27:27,580 --> 00:27:28,580
Get in.

448
00:27:30,350 --> 00:27:31,350
Get in.

449
00:27:34,790 --> 00:27:37,120
You should call him first.
He might be asleep.

450
00:27:37,520 --> 00:27:41,360
With us, showing up unannounced
gets you an even bigger welcome.

451
00:27:41,630 --> 00:27:43,190
We need to establish your place with us.

452
00:27:43,530 --> 00:27:46,130
That may be true for you, but it's rude.

453
00:27:46,260 --> 00:27:47,530
Trust me on this.

454
00:27:49,770 --> 00:27:50,940
Then at least text him.

455
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:28,040
Careful. It's slippery, you'll get hurt.

456
00:28:34,750 --> 00:28:37,120
I don't feel like it. You go in alone.

457
00:29:10,780 --> 00:29:11,950
Director Shin.

458
00:29:12,220 --> 00:29:15,320
Since you're getting married,
you'll be getting a lot of press.

459
00:29:15,890 --> 00:29:19,060
I got a suit that would look great on you.
I got it at cost.

460
00:29:19,790 --> 00:29:22,230
I've only seen you in a suit a few times,

461
00:29:22,760 --> 00:29:24,700
but with my professional eye,

462
00:29:24,760 --> 00:29:26,260
I thought there was some room
for improvement.

463
00:29:26,530 --> 00:29:27,530
Jin Ju.

464
00:29:28,030 --> 00:29:31,400
- Hurry up. I have to get to a wedding.
- Yes, sir.

465
00:29:34,610 --> 00:29:37,940
What should I wear?
The press is going to swarm the place.

466
00:29:39,810 --> 00:29:42,480
My boss sent me to give you this.

467
00:29:42,810 --> 00:29:44,650
Take it back. I can't accept this.

468
00:29:44,720 --> 00:29:47,090
My boss is just a very generous person.

469
00:29:47,090 --> 00:29:48,150
This is way too much.

470
00:29:48,720 --> 00:29:51,790
They say even fish can't live
in water that's too pure.

471
00:29:53,660 --> 00:29:54,790
Are you trying...

472
00:29:55,730 --> 00:29:56,830
to lecture me?

473
00:30:05,440 --> 00:30:08,210
I got the suit.
We should grab a meal sometime.

474
00:30:10,980 --> 00:30:14,180
(We're ready for surgery.)

475
00:30:19,120 --> 00:30:21,790
Did your interview run late yesterday?

476
00:30:23,920 --> 00:30:25,120
Are you sure he's your dad?

477
00:30:25,590 --> 00:30:26,690
I hope so.

478
00:30:26,820 --> 00:30:29,830
He's so young.
He said he was 20 when I was born.

479
00:30:30,230 --> 00:30:32,230
We're scheduled for a DNA test on Monday.

480
00:30:32,430 --> 00:30:36,000
- What's he like?
- I bet he was a real looker in his day.

481
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:38,900
- He's single.
- Sure he's not a con artist?

482
00:30:38,900 --> 00:30:39,940
Nowadays, it's gotten more sophisticated.

483
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:43,210
What could he possibly con me out of?
It's not like I have anything.

484
00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:45,980
We'll do the test, and if it's negative,

485
00:30:45,980 --> 00:30:48,550
I'll just say goodbye,
and that will be it.

486
00:30:49,350 --> 00:30:50,350
But...

487
00:30:50,820 --> 00:30:52,150
My heart just...

488
00:30:54,850 --> 00:30:56,650
Shoot. I have to go.

489
00:30:57,050 --> 00:30:58,320
If your boss is calling, then this...

490
00:30:58,390 --> 00:31:00,530
No, it's my manager.
He's got a short fuse...

491
00:31:02,330 --> 00:31:03,460
I'll see you later.

492
00:31:18,340 --> 00:31:20,550
(Hospital Director, Shin Ju Shin)

493
00:31:30,620 --> 00:31:32,560
(Kim Jin Ju)

494
00:31:33,990 --> 00:31:34,990
(I got the suit...)

495
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:43,030
Thank you for the suit.
Are you free for dinner tonight?

496
00:31:53,440 --> 00:31:56,080
Thank you for the suit.
Can you do dinner tonight?

497
00:31:58,880 --> 00:31:59,980
Yes, Director Shin.

498
00:32:37,560 --> 00:32:39,520
- Kim Jin Ju?
- Yes.

499
00:32:53,240 --> 00:32:54,270
Did you have lunch?

500
00:32:54,970 --> 00:32:57,340
I just had some snacks
at my friend's place.

501
00:32:57,680 --> 00:32:58,680
You must be hungry, then.

502
00:32:58,940 --> 00:33:00,140
What about you, Director Shin?

503
00:33:00,750 --> 00:33:01,750
You're friends...

504
00:33:03,150 --> 00:33:04,150
with Geum Ba Ra?

505
00:33:05,950 --> 00:33:06,950
Yes.

506
00:33:08,090 --> 00:33:09,620
Are both of you still single?

507
00:33:10,550 --> 00:33:11,560
A boyfriend.

508
00:33:13,790 --> 00:33:14,790
Right.

509
00:33:15,790 --> 00:33:16,930
So what do you do for fun?

510
00:33:18,800 --> 00:33:20,160
I enjoy my work.

511
00:33:26,700 --> 00:33:27,740
Ladies first.

512
00:33:43,850 --> 00:33:45,290
They're Baccarat glasses.

513
00:33:46,590 --> 00:33:48,290
Since you just moved here from abroad,

514
00:33:48,560 --> 00:33:50,560
I figured you might not have anything.

515
00:33:51,460 --> 00:33:53,100
And these are things you'll need.

516
00:33:54,400 --> 00:33:57,500
Clients, gallery owners, and reporters...

517
00:33:58,100 --> 00:34:00,570
will all be dropping by your studio
frequently now.

518
00:34:04,780 --> 00:34:07,080
Have you tried this?

519
00:34:11,020 --> 00:34:12,020
Mr. Kim.

520
00:34:15,350 --> 00:34:16,690
Aren't you lonely?

521
00:34:17,390 --> 00:34:20,090
Isn't everyone a little lonely?

522
00:34:20,660 --> 00:34:22,190
The character for "person..."

523
00:34:23,930 --> 00:34:25,660
shows two people...

524
00:34:26,460 --> 00:34:27,830
leaning on each other.

525
00:34:30,630 --> 00:34:33,800
It's only natural for us
to rely on each other to get by.

526
00:34:35,040 --> 00:34:36,910
That's what my mother used to say.

527
00:34:40,750 --> 00:34:41,750
I...

528
00:34:42,650 --> 00:34:44,550
at least have my beautiful daughter.

529
00:34:45,720 --> 00:34:46,880
Are you offering...

530
00:34:47,650 --> 00:34:48,820
to be my friend?

531
00:34:52,360 --> 00:34:53,560
Just...

532
00:34:54,260 --> 00:34:55,260
a friend?

533
00:34:57,090 --> 00:34:58,500
Someone I can confide in.

534
00:35:05,040 --> 00:35:06,040
How about me?

535
00:35:08,040 --> 00:35:10,540
Have you tried this?

536
00:35:11,610 --> 00:35:13,210
This wine is on a whole other level.

537
00:35:13,340 --> 00:35:14,910
It's from my private collection.

538
00:35:20,220 --> 00:35:23,790
You know, you really play favorites.

539
00:35:24,520 --> 00:35:26,760
- To CEO Ju Yeong Ae...
- Hyun Ran Hee.

540
00:35:29,630 --> 00:35:30,730
What do you think you're doing?

541
00:35:31,560 --> 00:35:33,400
- Mr. Kim.
- I'm...

542
00:35:33,900 --> 00:35:34,900
Kim Young Jun.

543
00:35:38,040 --> 00:35:39,270
Did you forget my name too?

544
00:35:40,740 --> 00:35:41,810
I...

545
00:35:42,740 --> 00:35:43,740
Are you...

546
00:35:49,580 --> 00:35:51,520
No way. Absolutely not.

547
00:35:51,750 --> 00:35:53,450
I was in a car accident in Germany.

548
00:35:53,780 --> 00:35:54,790
A bad one.

549
00:35:57,990 --> 00:35:59,960
- You completely forgot all about me.
- Did you...

550
00:36:00,320 --> 00:36:01,630
get a whole new face?

551
00:36:01,630 --> 00:36:02,930
Let's just say you forgot about me.

552
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:06,630
But did you also completely forget
about the child you abandoned?

553
00:36:07,300 --> 00:36:09,200
How can you live so carefree
with a clear conscience?

554
00:36:09,670 --> 00:36:12,140
- Who says I abandoned her? She had a dad.
- I don't want to speak with you.

555
00:36:14,570 --> 00:36:16,140
And I hope I never see you again.

556
00:36:16,340 --> 00:36:17,710
Wasn't his name Pyeon Seung Jae?

557
00:36:18,380 --> 00:36:20,110
The one whose father was a doctor.

558
00:36:20,110 --> 00:36:22,150
I heard from him that you went to Japan.

559
00:36:28,050 --> 00:36:29,050
What about our child?

560
00:36:32,820 --> 00:36:33,920
In Germany?

561
00:36:34,290 --> 00:36:36,790
The daughter of the woman
who worked for our family for ages...

562
00:36:37,730 --> 00:36:40,300
moved to Japan, did very well,
and opened a big restaurant.

563
00:36:40,560 --> 00:36:42,100
She was born at our house.

564
00:36:43,030 --> 00:36:44,030
I think I remember hearing that.

565
00:36:44,100 --> 00:36:47,400
I gave her the baby and went to Germany,
but had an accident upon arrival.

566
00:36:47,470 --> 00:36:50,940
My recovery took a long time,
but I was determined to make it through.

567
00:36:51,680 --> 00:36:55,110
After ten years, I tried to contact her,
but I couldn't get to her.

568
00:36:56,080 --> 00:36:59,480
I was worried, but I trusted her
to raise our daughter well.

569
00:36:59,650 --> 00:37:01,920
After everything our family did for her.

570
00:37:03,320 --> 00:37:06,660
A few years ago, I went to look for them,
but her restaurant was gone.

571
00:37:06,720 --> 00:37:08,760
So I asked around
at the neighboring shops.

572
00:37:09,890 --> 00:37:12,100
They told me she had died
just days after I left.

573
00:37:12,400 --> 00:37:14,730
- Why?
- It was her Yakuza boyfriend.

574
00:37:16,070 --> 00:37:17,900
It was a crime of passion, apparently.

575
00:37:20,070 --> 00:37:21,070
And our daughter?

576
00:37:24,740 --> 00:37:25,980
Did something happen to her?

577
00:37:26,710 --> 00:37:29,480
All I could find out was
that she was brought back to Korea.

578
00:37:29,550 --> 00:37:31,050
When? Who brought her back?

579
00:37:31,250 --> 00:37:33,820
There was a Korean lady at the eatery.

580
00:37:34,390 --> 00:37:35,520
She brought her back...

581
00:37:35,820 --> 00:37:37,090
What was her name?

582
00:37:37,490 --> 00:37:38,790
How would I know?

583
00:37:38,890 --> 00:37:40,420
I was only there one night.

584
00:37:40,520 --> 00:37:42,730
All I remember is she had a round face.

585
00:37:44,200 --> 00:37:45,830
There were no records of her?

586
00:37:51,170 --> 00:37:52,400
I had no idea.

587
00:37:55,170 --> 00:37:56,170
I just thought she was in Japan,

588
00:37:57,580 --> 00:37:59,040
living a good life.

589
00:38:03,480 --> 00:38:05,180
So, is that woman raising her, then?

590
00:38:05,550 --> 00:38:06,850
I went to the police,

591
00:38:07,480 --> 00:38:11,460
but there was nothing they could do.
So, grasping at straws, I hired a PI.

592
00:38:14,890 --> 00:38:16,260
He said he couldn't make any promises.

593
00:38:20,500 --> 00:38:22,900
If she's alive, right now she'd be...

594
00:38:26,140 --> 00:38:27,500
You never even registered her birth?

595
00:38:29,240 --> 00:38:30,440
Are you blaming me now?

596
00:38:31,240 --> 00:38:32,280
You just dumped her on me...

597
00:38:32,280 --> 00:38:34,380
when my family was falling apart,
and then disappeared.

598
00:38:35,950 --> 00:38:39,320
She'd always adored me,
so I assumed she'd raise her well.

599
00:38:42,620 --> 00:38:44,120
I had a necklace made
with her name and put it on her.

600
00:38:46,060 --> 00:38:48,560
What name did you use?

601
00:38:48,760 --> 00:38:50,130
Her paternal grandmother's.

602
00:38:50,930 --> 00:38:53,160
The characters for Jin and Ju.

603
00:38:55,370 --> 00:38:58,400
Kim Jin Ju?

604
00:39:05,540 --> 00:39:08,550
Don't tell me it's that Kim Jin Ju.

605
00:39:08,850 --> 00:39:09,850
Hello?

606
00:39:10,610 --> 00:39:11,620
No, it can't be.

607
00:39:12,480 --> 00:39:13,480
Hello.

608
00:39:14,790 --> 00:39:17,350
Yes, I'll check with the gallery.

609
00:39:20,660 --> 00:39:22,230
There's a wrapped painting in my room.

610
00:39:22,230 --> 00:39:23,590
It's next to my desk. Go get it.

611
00:39:23,760 --> 00:39:24,760
Okay.

612
00:39:27,930 --> 00:39:29,070
Is she new?

613
00:39:29,770 --> 00:39:31,270
Momo's new stylist. She started last week.

614
00:39:31,540 --> 00:39:34,070
- Is she trustworthy?
- Yes.

615
00:39:35,940 --> 00:39:38,410
- Momo's new stylist.
- Kim Jin Ju?

616
00:39:38,910 --> 00:39:40,140
Did you run a background check on her?

617
00:39:40,410 --> 00:39:41,410
No.

618
00:39:41,550 --> 00:39:42,610
You need to.

619
00:39:43,010 --> 00:39:46,380
You can't be too careful these days.
She could leak information.

620
00:39:47,720 --> 00:39:50,390
- Is she discreet?
- She's quiet and seems composed.

621
00:39:50,990 --> 00:39:52,920
You know how many people
talk behind your back.

622
00:39:53,260 --> 00:39:54,360
You can't judge a book by its cover.

623
00:39:55,490 --> 00:39:57,730
That sponsored bracelet
that went missing last year...

624
00:39:58,330 --> 00:39:59,900
I'm sure that was an inside job.

625
00:40:01,430 --> 00:40:02,430
What do her parents do?

626
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:04,270
I don't know that...

627
00:40:17,780 --> 00:40:18,780
It's good, isn't it?

628
00:40:20,120 --> 00:40:21,120
Yes.

629
00:40:21,750 --> 00:40:23,190
Is James treating you well?

630
00:40:23,450 --> 00:40:26,020
- Yes.
- Where did you work before this?

631
00:40:26,520 --> 00:40:28,990
I worked under Park Min Ja.

632
00:40:31,560 --> 00:40:33,930
You don't need to use honorifics
for her when you speak to me.

633
00:40:34,630 --> 00:40:36,270
Does Park Min Ja outrank me?

634
00:40:37,770 --> 00:40:38,770
Yes.

635
00:40:39,670 --> 00:40:42,070
Order a Coke.
Everyone has Coke with pizza, right?

636
00:40:42,540 --> 00:40:44,240
I don't really drink soda.

637
00:40:45,240 --> 00:40:48,310
Good. If you're next to Momo,
constantly sipping on things like that,

638
00:40:48,380 --> 00:40:49,980
how difficult do you think
that makes it for her?

639
00:40:50,480 --> 00:40:52,050
She's dieting like her life depends on it,

640
00:40:52,580 --> 00:40:53,880
even when she has such a big appetite.

641
00:40:56,750 --> 00:40:57,960
So, what do your parents do?

642
00:41:02,090 --> 00:41:03,290
Are they divorced?

643
00:41:06,930 --> 00:41:10,300
I grew up in an orphanage.

644
00:41:25,350 --> 00:41:28,490
Don't worry, CEO Hyun.
I hired her because she's a hard worker,

645
00:41:28,850 --> 00:41:30,790
and you know I'm a better judge
of character than anyone.

646
00:41:31,460 --> 00:41:32,990
I wouldn't pair Momo with just anyone.

647
00:41:38,330 --> 00:41:39,600
We'll have to wait and see.

648
00:41:39,600 --> 00:41:41,470
How she's always walking on eggshells...

649
00:41:41,530 --> 00:41:42,800
She's better than some clumsy fool.

650
00:41:42,870 --> 00:41:44,740
I fear she's a wolf in sheep's clothing.

651
00:41:45,600 --> 00:41:47,640
Mom, you can be a little too
suspicious of people.

652
00:41:55,450 --> 00:41:56,610
(Momo)

653
00:41:56,680 --> 00:41:59,020
Tell Jin Ju to come up before she leaves.

654
00:42:10,530 --> 00:42:12,230
You'll get an upset stomach. Slow down.

655
00:42:12,960 --> 00:42:14,160
Have some milk with it.

656
00:42:17,230 --> 00:42:18,740
Mom, did you just get here?

657
00:42:19,670 --> 00:42:20,670
No.

658
00:42:21,100 --> 00:42:23,610
Then did you make these yourself?

659
00:42:24,940 --> 00:42:26,780
It's not like making a sandwich
takes that long.

660
00:42:28,250 --> 00:42:31,150
Jin Ju, your hair is so lovely and thick.

661
00:42:32,480 --> 00:42:33,580
Let me compare.

662
00:42:39,060 --> 00:42:41,860
My hair just keeps getting
thinner with age...

663
00:42:45,460 --> 00:42:46,460
Mom.

664
00:42:48,100 --> 00:42:49,170
Look at how thick it is.

665
00:43:02,450 --> 00:43:03,580
Why are you so tense?

666
00:43:04,150 --> 00:43:05,180
You're making me uncomfortable.

667
00:43:10,690 --> 00:43:11,690
Nice earrings.

668
00:43:12,660 --> 00:43:14,830
- Drink up.
- I'll take my time.

669
00:43:18,900 --> 00:43:19,900
Are you a lightweight?

670
00:43:20,430 --> 00:43:21,470
I can't drink much...

671
00:43:22,000 --> 00:43:23,530
My driver will take you home.

672
00:43:25,900 --> 00:43:28,270
I couldn't possibly take your ride, sir.

673
00:43:28,840 --> 00:43:29,840
I live nearby.

674
00:43:30,440 --> 00:43:31,480
I'm going to walk to sober up anyway.

675
00:43:34,080 --> 00:43:35,080
Were they a gift?

676
00:43:37,410 --> 00:43:39,350
They said they were in my baby blanket.

677
00:43:41,650 --> 00:43:42,890
Do you resent your parents?

678
00:43:44,590 --> 00:43:46,720
I'm sure they had their reasons.

679
00:43:48,260 --> 00:43:49,560
That's a wise way to think about it.

680
00:43:51,730 --> 00:43:53,630
Did Momo ever give you
a hard time at work?

681
00:43:54,400 --> 00:43:55,430
Not at all.

682
00:43:55,770 --> 00:43:57,400
She was a total nightmare.

683
00:43:58,340 --> 00:43:59,500
Are you managing to save any money?

684
00:44:00,740 --> 00:44:02,410
- I am.
- What for?

685
00:44:03,370 --> 00:44:04,370
To get your own place?

686
00:44:04,710 --> 00:44:07,280
First, I want to take a trip.

687
00:44:07,480 --> 00:44:08,550
Where to?

688
00:44:09,380 --> 00:44:12,420
- Japan.
- For the food? Shopping?

689
00:44:12,480 --> 00:44:13,480
Both.

690
00:44:15,490 --> 00:44:16,490
Lots of expenses will come up.

691
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:24,630
(DNA Analysis Report)

692
00:44:28,400 --> 00:44:29,400
(DNA Analysis Report)

693
00:44:29,470 --> 00:44:31,800
(DNA Test Report)

694
00:44:41,650 --> 00:44:42,650
Here.

695
00:44:45,720 --> 00:44:46,720
It's a gift certificate.

696
00:44:47,120 --> 00:44:48,720
- No, I couldn't.
- I had it lying around.

697
00:44:49,190 --> 00:44:50,290
I don't need it.

698
00:44:51,820 --> 00:44:53,890
Go on, take it. It was a gift.

699
00:44:56,390 --> 00:44:58,500
But you already treated me
to such a nice dinner.

700
00:45:01,500 --> 00:45:02,770
Thank you.

701
00:45:06,770 --> 00:45:07,800
So is the job a good fit for you?

702
00:45:08,910 --> 00:45:09,910
Yes.

703
00:45:10,370 --> 00:45:12,140
(DNA Test Report)

704
00:45:18,380 --> 00:45:20,880
(Subjects: Kim Young Jun, Kim Jin Ju)

705
00:45:21,250 --> 00:45:25,960
(Paternity Probability: Non-match)

706
00:45:36,700 --> 00:45:38,770
I have plenty of great paintings,
you know.

707
00:45:38,940 --> 00:45:41,200
I mean, we're not talking
about a couple of grand here.

708
00:45:41,440 --> 00:45:43,540
Then just consider it a loan.

709
00:45:43,740 --> 00:45:45,140
Keep it on your wall for a few years.

710
00:45:45,510 --> 00:45:47,310
- Mr. Ha.
- Yes?

711
00:45:47,510 --> 00:45:49,480
Would you rather take this back
and continue...

712
00:45:49,480 --> 00:45:50,910
your relationship with Yong Joong and me?

713
00:45:51,080 --> 00:45:54,480
Or should I take this piece
and we call it quits today?

714
00:45:55,890 --> 00:45:57,690
Give it here. I'll take it back.

715
00:45:58,460 --> 00:46:00,660
Manager Yoon, take this back to my office.

716
00:46:02,290 --> 00:46:05,330
Goodness, I'm no match for you,
Reporter Geum.

717
00:46:05,860 --> 00:46:08,000
It's okay to let your junior win
every once in a while.

718
00:46:08,070 --> 00:46:09,730
What do you mean, junior?

719
00:46:10,000 --> 00:46:11,700
Even your rejections are clever.

720
00:46:11,970 --> 00:46:14,040
- Some drinks, please.
- Yes, sir.

721
00:46:14,340 --> 00:46:16,410
Don't you feel peckish?
Shall we order something?

722
00:46:16,410 --> 00:46:17,540
It's the perfect time for a snack.

723
00:46:17,610 --> 00:46:19,910
What are you in the mood for? My treat.

724
00:46:19,980 --> 00:46:22,680
Especially after the huge spread
you gave me last time.

725
00:46:22,880 --> 00:46:25,020
- My pleasure.
- Me too.

726
00:46:26,220 --> 00:46:27,350
How about some jokbal?

727
00:46:28,090 --> 00:46:29,990
On second thought,
that's not really fitting for you.

728
00:46:30,250 --> 00:46:33,360
- I'm willing to try it.
- Wait, you've never had jokbal?

729
00:46:34,620 --> 00:46:35,630
No.

730
00:46:36,930 --> 00:46:38,600
Let's go with lamb and hummus instead.

731
00:46:39,330 --> 00:46:41,800
- But you can't get that delivered.
- I'm James.

732
00:46:46,540 --> 00:46:48,740
Is Jin Ju out on assignment?

733
00:47:04,350 --> 00:47:08,990
<i>I should've told you</i>

734
00:47:11,460 --> 00:47:17,570
<i>That I loved you</i>

735
00:47:19,340 --> 00:47:24,040
<i>That without you</i>

736
00:47:26,010 --> 00:47:31,820
<i>I can't live on</i>

737
00:47:33,950 --> 00:47:39,090
<i>That I love you</i>

738
00:47:40,620 --> 00:47:45,700
<i>I should have said it</i>

739
00:47:48,470 --> 00:47:55,470
<i>But I hesitated</i>

740
00:47:55,710 --> 00:48:01,610
<i>And my love is gone</i>

741
00:48:04,110 --> 00:48:06,420
<i>I gave you my heart</i>

742
00:48:11,450 --> 00:48:14,020
<i>I gave you my tears</i>

743
00:48:18,600 --> 00:48:21,160
<i>And I gave you my dreams</i>

744
00:48:25,300 --> 00:48:30,710
<i>But you drifted away</i>

745
00:48:31,680 --> 00:48:37,410
<i>My love is far away</i>

746
00:48:45,260 --> 00:48:47,390
What do I have to do, go pray at a temple?

747
00:48:48,860 --> 00:48:50,930
I just can't give her up. I can't.

748
00:49:13,280 --> 00:49:14,890
Everything...

749
00:49:21,420 --> 00:49:24,160
All of it...

750
00:49:26,900 --> 00:49:28,200
(Geum Ba Ra)

751
00:49:37,940 --> 00:49:39,080
Hey, Ba Ra.

752
00:49:40,380 --> 00:49:41,410
Have you been drinking?

753
00:49:42,780 --> 00:49:43,780
A little.

754
00:49:45,650 --> 00:49:48,350
Are the results not a match?

755
00:49:52,160 --> 00:49:53,360
Not a match.

756
00:49:56,930 --> 00:49:58,190
With my luck, who was I kidding?

757
00:49:59,760 --> 00:50:02,170
I really had my hopes up all weekend.

758
00:50:02,970 --> 00:50:04,470
And I was so happy.

759
00:50:05,170 --> 00:50:08,070
- Go to bed.
- You pathetic fool.

760
00:50:11,270 --> 00:50:13,580
Pathetic or not,

761
00:50:14,340 --> 00:50:15,380
I'm still...

762
00:50:15,910 --> 00:50:17,910
your biggest fan.

763
00:50:25,160 --> 00:50:26,620
That venomous witch.

764
00:50:57,820 --> 00:51:00,490
Careful. It's slippery, you'll get hurt.

765
00:51:01,020 --> 00:51:03,860
Where does it hurt? Is it your spine?
Your tailbone?

766
00:51:05,260 --> 00:51:06,300
I don't know.

767
00:51:08,670 --> 00:51:09,800
Ju Shin's here.

768
00:51:16,870 --> 00:51:18,610
Sorry.

769
00:51:31,120 --> 00:51:32,360
Are you shocked?

770
00:51:34,490 --> 00:51:35,560
Shocked about what?

771
00:51:45,170 --> 00:51:46,240
I'm going.

772
00:51:59,650 --> 00:52:05,160
(Available)

773
00:52:06,520 --> 00:52:09,490
- Myeonghui-dong, please.
- You should get off first. It's closer.

774
00:52:09,990 --> 00:52:10,990
Myeonghui-dong, please.

775
00:52:18,970 --> 00:52:20,470
See? Just listen to me from now on.

776
00:52:30,250 --> 00:52:31,510
Is there a convenience store nearby?

777
00:52:31,650 --> 00:52:32,720
They're everywhere.

778
00:52:34,880 --> 00:52:35,890
Don't worry about it.

779
00:52:36,890 --> 00:52:38,820
Sir, the Itanic Palace, please.

780
00:52:39,120 --> 00:52:40,660
No, Myeonghui-dong, please.

781
00:52:50,370 --> 00:52:51,370
Right here, please.

782
00:52:56,310 --> 00:52:57,310
What looks good?

783
00:53:15,690 --> 00:53:17,990
- I'll get fat if I eat this at night.
- You need to gain some.

784
00:53:21,000 --> 00:53:22,230
If you get fired for gaining weight,

785
00:53:22,900 --> 00:53:23,900
you've got me to lean on.

786
00:53:24,970 --> 00:53:26,170
Then I'll get ice cream, too.

787
00:53:31,470 --> 00:53:32,980
It's the first day
since we confessed our love,

788
00:53:33,440 --> 00:53:34,510
but this is a pretty weak celebration.

789
00:53:35,680 --> 00:53:36,680
It's plenty.

790
00:53:37,650 --> 00:53:38,780
So I'm your number one, right?

791
00:53:41,720 --> 00:53:43,020
I'm happy being third.

792
00:53:44,220 --> 00:53:46,890
James, Momo, and then me.

793
00:53:48,220 --> 00:53:49,230
Whatever.

794
00:53:51,030 --> 00:53:52,100
There's a taxi.

795
00:53:55,100 --> 00:53:56,100
Go on.

796
00:54:29,370 --> 00:54:30,470
Sweet dreams.

797
00:55:24,050 --> 00:55:27,260
Isn't that the story? The broke girl
who's all alone snags the prince?

798
00:55:29,430 --> 00:55:30,990
Your bones look fine.

799
00:55:32,000 --> 00:55:33,500
Is it a sprained ligament then?

800
00:55:34,530 --> 00:55:35,730
Should I get some physical therapy?

801
00:55:36,800 --> 00:55:39,900
We need to know how much production costs,
like talent fees, have spiked.

802
00:55:39,970 --> 00:55:43,710
We need concrete figures,
not just what the PR people are saying.

803
00:55:43,770 --> 00:55:44,810
Get some solid quotes...

804
00:55:44,810 --> 00:55:46,610
from production company CEOs
or top executives.

805
00:55:46,940 --> 00:55:49,080
- Understood.
- Kwon Woo Seok.

806
00:55:49,150 --> 00:55:50,810
- Sir?
- Are you giving me an eye test?

807
00:55:51,450 --> 00:55:53,820
You're fast, but why have there been
so many typos recently?

808
00:55:53,820 --> 00:55:54,920
I'm sorry, sir.

809
00:55:57,750 --> 00:56:00,490
I know Director Park Tae Won at Juplus.
Want an introduction?

810
00:56:01,020 --> 00:56:02,260
I would really appreciate that.

811
00:56:03,130 --> 00:56:06,630
- Tuesday. The highlight of my week.
- Because of the black bean noodles?

812
00:56:06,700 --> 00:56:09,070
It's better than most Chinese restaurants.

813
00:56:09,130 --> 00:56:11,670
I heard the Friday special
at the Shinpyeong Daily is beef bone soup.

814
00:56:13,570 --> 00:56:14,570
Hello?

815
00:56:15,510 --> 00:56:18,140
Looks like she's got a boyfriend.

816
00:56:19,280 --> 00:56:21,280
The caller ID says
"Manager Kim, Self-Reliance Center."

817
00:56:22,980 --> 00:56:26,320
He knows the exact date
you were brought to Minjin Church.

818
00:56:26,680 --> 00:56:29,620
How old is he?

819
00:56:30,050 --> 00:56:32,560
He was born in 1968.
His name is Kim Gwang Cheol.

820
00:56:33,160 --> 00:56:34,320
If he's your biological father,

821
00:56:34,760 --> 00:56:37,790
then you were never Geum Ba Ra,
but Kim Ba Ra all along.

822
00:56:47,800 --> 00:56:50,840
I heard from Manager Kim
at the Self-Reliance Center.

823
00:56:51,440 --> 00:56:53,310
My name is Geum Ba Ra.

824
00:56:54,540 --> 00:56:55,750
(Kim Gwang Cheol)

825
00:57:14,230 --> 00:57:15,800
(Kim Gwang Cheol)

826
00:57:26,310 --> 00:57:27,310
Hello?

827
00:57:27,380 --> 00:57:30,010
(Just got your text.)

828
00:57:31,180 --> 00:57:32,180
Hello.

829
00:57:32,350 --> 00:57:35,220
(From the center...)

830
00:57:35,250 --> 00:57:37,120
(You live in Seoul?)

831
00:57:37,120 --> 00:57:38,120
Yes.

832
00:57:38,650 --> 00:57:42,690
(When are you free?
I'm available right now.)

833
00:57:42,890 --> 00:57:46,130
(Just tell me where, and I'll head over.)

834
00:57:46,800 --> 00:57:49,000
(It won't take me more than an hour.)

835
00:57:57,470 --> 00:57:59,440
Does the ER have an orthopedist?

836
00:59:36,410 --> 00:59:37,810
(Kim Gwang Cheol)

837
00:59:57,390 --> 00:59:58,430
Geum Ba Ra?

838
01:00:11,110 --> 01:00:14,640
December 21, 1999,

839
01:00:14,980 --> 01:00:16,150
at Minjin Church?

840
01:00:16,750 --> 01:00:17,750
Yes.

841
01:00:19,420 --> 01:00:20,720
Are you ready to order?

842
01:00:21,050 --> 01:00:22,050
Coffee.

843
01:00:22,350 --> 01:00:23,450
An Americano?

844
01:00:23,890 --> 01:00:25,820
- Yes.
- Hot?

845
01:00:25,890 --> 01:00:27,090
No, iced.

846
01:00:28,160 --> 01:00:29,160
I'll have the same.

847
01:00:33,000 --> 01:00:36,030
I looked into it,
and on that day, two babies...

848
01:00:36,830 --> 01:00:37,830
Yes...

849
01:01:22,910 --> 01:01:25,750
(Doctor Shin)

850
01:01:25,880 --> 01:01:28,150
When will you stop being so formal?
It's going to become a habit.

851
01:01:28,350 --> 01:01:29,650
It'll become a habit.

852
01:01:29,650 --> 01:01:31,850
Reporter Geum
is going to be devastated. This is awful.

853
01:01:32,120 --> 01:01:34,260
- What are we going to do?
- Are you sure about this?

854
01:01:34,320 --> 01:01:36,190
But you know how people
can have a change of heart.

855
01:01:36,690 --> 01:01:40,230
- Having second thoughts?
- I can have you all fired! Hey, Lee Shim!

856
01:01:40,300 --> 01:01:42,230
- Park Soo!
- You want me to be honest?

857
01:01:42,300 --> 01:01:44,070
You should be,
especially with a good drink like this.

858
01:01:44,130 --> 01:01:45,940
Don't you know what people look for
in a marriage prospect?

859
01:01:45,940 --> 01:01:47,870
I don't. All I know is love.

860
01:01:47,940 --> 01:01:50,670
- Have you actually said "I love you?"
- Of course I've been in love.

861
01:01:50,740 --> 01:01:54,010
If you get adopted,
that lady won't volunteer anymore, right?

862
01:01:54,140 --> 01:01:55,280
She said she'd keep coming.

863
01:01:55,280 --> 01:01:57,510
Think it through so you have no regrets.

864
01:01:57,510 --> 01:01:59,420
- I won't.
- I was away at "school" all this time.

865
01:01:59,420 --> 01:02:00,580
You know what I mean by "school," right?

866
01:02:00,820 --> 01:02:02,180
- Kim Jin Ju.
- Yes?

867
01:02:02,180 --> 01:02:03,620
Ever think about getting on
an operating table?

868
01:02:04,250 --> 01:02:08,190
I don't know who'll be the first
to read this, but...

869
01:02:08,490 --> 01:02:09,790
What do you think of me?

870
01:02:09,790 --> 01:02:12,230
Not as chairman of the orphanage
or the hospital director,

871
01:02:12,290 --> 01:02:15,430
- but just as a man?
- I couldn't possibly...

872
01:02:17,070 --> 01:02:19,070
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)

